FT  22 OCT 93 / International Company News: Sales slip but ITT increases net
income
ITT, the US conglomerate, more than doubled third-quarter net income to
Dollars 252m, or Dollars 1.91 a share, from Dollars 113m, or 80 cents,last
year, on sales down from Dollars 5.5bn to Dollars 5.2bn.
But last year's third quarter was distorted by an after-tax gain of Dollars
622m on the sale of a stake in Alcatel; an after-tax charge of Dollars 759m
for insurance losses and Dollars 95m in hurricane insurance losses.
The latest period included an after-tax restructuring charge of Dollars 20m
and a Dollars 22m tax benefit.
